{"id":"cond-mat/0104081","submitter":"Kunal K. Das","authors":"Kunal Das and Thomas Bergeman","title":"Trends in Resonance Energy Shifts and Decay Rates for Bose Condensates\n  in a Harmonic Trap","comments":"10 figures. Accepted for publication in Physical Review A","journal-ref":"Phys. Rev. A 64, 013613 (2001)","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevA.64.013613","report-no":null,"categories":"cond-mat.stat-mech","license":null,"abstract":"  This is a study of quasi-discrete Bogoliubov quasi-particles in a spherically\nsymmetric harmonic trap. We first evaluate analytically the aymptotic energy\nshifts of the high energy modes and find them to have $1/sqrt(n)$ dependence on\nthe number of radial nodes, $n$, consistent with earlier semiclassical\ndiscussions. To address the question of the widths or decay rates, we attempt\nto clarify previous discussions by deriving an implicit equation for the widths\nfrom an assumption of exponential decay. Numerically, we study the trends in\nthe behavior of the widths as a function of temperature, energy, particle\nnumber and scattering lengths. In particular, we find that the width due to\nLandau decay rises rapidly at low $n$ and then declines, while the Beliaev\ndecay rate rises slowly with $n$. As temperature goes to zero, Beliaev decay\nreaches a constant (>0 for n>0), while the Landau decay rate goes to zero. The\ndecay rate is approximately linear in the s-wave scattering length.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 4 Apr 2001 19:29:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-07"}
